The donation is as a result of his passion love and care for Sierra Leoneans that were affected  by the mudslide and the flooding that affected their houses  and cause  the loss of lives  of many  Sierra Leoneans.

Receiving the donation on behalf of the government of Sierra Leone the ONS representative in charged at the old school centre thank MaCikz and patron for the wonderful gesture. 
As a young person this is a step in the right direction and I urge other Sierra Leoneans  home and abroad to work in the same direction especially when crisis like this occurs.
